{{ill|Takeinadane|ja|建稲種命|simple|User:Immanuelle/Takeinadane|en:draft|Takeinadane|fr}} was a Japanese warrior in the [[2nd century|second century]]. He is worshipped as a {{ill|kami|en}} of {{ill|Atsuta Shrine|en}}.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Introduction {{!}} ATSUTA JINGU |url=https://www.atsutajingu.or.jp/en/intro/ |access-date=2023-12-09 |website=www.atsutajingu.or.jp}}</ref>

He was the brother of {{ill|Miyazu-hime|ja|宮簀媛|en}} the founder of {{ill|Atsuta Shrine|en}}.<ref name="Ponsonby-Fane-2016">{{Cite book |last=Ponsonby-Fane |first=R. A. B. |title=Studies In Shinto & Shrines |date=2016-05-11 |publisher=Routledge |isbn=978-1-138-98322-9 |edition=1st |language=English |chapter=Atsuta Jingu}}</ref>{{rp|435}}{{Dead link|date=December 2023}} The {{ill|Owari clan|en}} established the {{ill|Atsuta Shrine|en}} in 192, and held the position of the shrine's high priest since ancient times, passing it down from generation to generation.<ref name="Naito-1975">{{Cite book |last=Naito |first=Toho |title=Choshu Zasshi (張州雑志) |publisher=Aichi-ken Kyōdo Shiryō Kankō-kai |year=1975 |doi=10.11501/9537297}}</ref> {{ill|Yamato Takeru|en}} and {{ill|Miyazu-hime|ja|宮簀媛|en}} and her brother {{ill|Takeinadane|ja|建稲種命|simple|User:Immanuelle/Takeinadane|en:draft|Takeinadane}} are worshipped at the shrine.<ref name="Ponsonby-Fane-2016" />{{rp|429}}

He is also worshipped at {{ill|Tagata Shrine|en}} alongside his wife Tamahime.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Small village gets real big at ancient celebration |url=https://www.mcasiwakuni.marines.mil/Iwakuni-News/News-Stories/News-Article-Display/Article/506486/small-village-gets-real-big-at-ancient-celebration/https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mcasiwakuni.marines.mil%2FIwakuni-News%2FNews-Stories%2FNews-Article-Display%2FArticle%2F506486%2Fsmall-village-gets-real-big-at-ancient-celebration%2F |access-date=2023-11-18 |website=Marine Corps Air Station Iwakuni, Japan |language=en-US}}</ref>

He and his wife had two sons and four daughters.<ref name=":0" /> After his death his wife set up {{ill|Tagata Shrine|en}} in his honor among other deities.<ref name=":0" />

